Getting WSL working with Git and Docker:

Install GitBash
	- This is used only for its credential manager
	- Located at /mnt/c/Program\ Files/Git/mingw64/libexec/git-core/git-credential-wincred.exe or /mnt/c/Program\ Files/Git/mingw64/libexec/git-core/git-credential-manager.exe

Install Docker
Once Logged in and running, go to settings
General -> Expose Daemon on Localhost

Install Ubuntu from the Windows Store
Open Ubuntu and make user

sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade
sudo apt-get install docker.io

mkdir /c
echo 'sudo mount --bind /mnt/c /c' >> ~/.bashrc
sudo visudo
Append "{username} ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /bin/mount"

echo 'export DOCKER_HOST=tcp://localhost:2375' >> ~/.bashrc

source ~/.bashrc
